SWEBS - stands for Swimple Web Server

Written completly(for now) in C++

Main goal is to create a fully portable and simple in use webserver(sorry for my english is not native)

V 0.1
just runs an index.html from ./www

V 0.1.a

You can specify port, root dir and path to fpm socket file

for example:
./simple_server --port 8080 --directory ./www --socket /run/php/php7.4-fpm.sock


V 0.1.b

You can use swebs as a proxy for other web service and you can use https

for example
./simple_server --port 8080 --directory ./www --socket /run/php/php7.4-fpm.sock --proxy-port 80 --proxy-host example.com --proxy-protocol-v1 --ssl-cert /path/to/your/certificate.pem --ssl-port 8443


V 0.1.c
simple_server is now multithreaded
